step_data.thought:
Based on my previous action, I clicked the 'Zoom In' button to reduce the area size since the message indicated the area was too large to export. Looking at the current page, I can see that the URL now shows 'map=9/42.8931/-74.1467', indicating we're at zoom level 9 (increased from level 8 previously).

I can also see that there are text boxes with coordinates values: 44.2708, -75.4239, -72.8696, 41.4839. These define the bounding box of the current selection. The page still appears to show a message that the area is too large: 'This area is too large to be exported as OpenStreetMap XML Data. Please zoom in or select a smaller area...'

I need to continue zooming in until the area becomes small enough for download. Let me click the 'Zoom In' button again to further increase the scale (zoom level).
